ORIGINAL WORK DECLARATION

The Anvil Method is a substantial original work that includes, but is
not limited to:

- Six-role adversarial orchestration system (EVALUATOR, Builder,
  Challenger, Proxy, Researcher, Tester)
- Dynamic complexity tier assessment (LIGHT, STANDARD, THOROUGH,
  RIGOROUS, MAXIMAL)
- Test-first sandbox methodology with before/after preservation
- Cryptographic passphrase-based completion verification
- Per-iteration learnings persistence system
- Safe-mode pre-flight safety checks
- Prompt template generator with OS-random passphrase generation
- Self-referential development loop via stop-hook exploitation

THIRD-PARTY ACKNOWLEDGMENTS

The Anvil Method builds upon the following open-source work:

- Ralph Wiggum iterative loop technique by Geoffrey Huntley
  (https://ghuntley.com/ralph/) — The foundational concept of
  self-referential AI development loops
- Ralph Loop Plugin (MIT License) — Original Claude Code marketplace
  plugin providing the stop-hook mechanism
- Boris Cherny — Inspired the antagonist review pattern

The original Ralph Loop Plugin is licensed under the MIT License.
